cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.GR 

This paper deals with key establishment protocols and their hardness relies on variations of the iterated LD problem and its generalizations. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), coding theory (cs.CC), and group theory (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses instantiations of the protocols using braid groups and their quotients, which suggests a possible connection to the category of symbolic computation (cs.SY).
